# Example ONLY. Copy to a chmod-600 file OUTSIDE the repo (e.g. /etc/box-binder/runtime.env)
# and fill from your secret backend. NEVER commit a filled copy — *.env is gitignored.
#
# JWT mode: provide the path to config.json (installed out-of-band, chmod 600).
#   RCLONE_CONFIG_BOX_BOX_CONFIG_FILE is already set by box-binder's secrets.env.
#
# CCG mode: inject the client credentials from your secret backend at runtime:
# BOX_BINDER_CLIENT_ID=__from_secret_backend__
# BOX_BINDER_CLIENT_SECRET=__from_secret_backend__
# BOX_BINDER_ENTERPRISE_ID=__from_secret_backend__
#
# Encrypted-conf fallback only:
# BOX_BINDER_RCLONE_PASS=__from_secret_backend__
